University of Sydney has run a 17-week diploma for Year 11 students at Scot's College to 'buy' entry to the university . 
  The program allows students to skip their year 12 exams without completing their HSC . 
  Education Minister Adrian Piccoli has called the shortcut 'unfair' and 'unacceptable' The University of Sydney shut down the pilot program this week . 
  Tuition, sporting and curricula fees for Scot's college reportedly top $30,000 . 
 